      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"1. REGGAE ETHICS is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 5 lengths at Goulburn in a handy 19.96 beating Major Ted. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Can measure up again. 2. RUGGED ETHICS was always prominent from this same draw last time and drew clear to score (29.92) in a Grade 5 over 520m at this track. Rates a leading chance again. 3. SAMMY ETHAN failed to come into contention last start after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won by a neck at this track (29.76) beating Zipping Hopkins in a Mix 1/2/3 on April 4. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Great chance to atone. 8. BLACK MYTH WAVE was out of placings last time (30.29) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing fifth and beaten 8 lengths. Has already won five times from this draw.\",\"runners\":[1,2,3,8],\"exclusive\":false}",
